Author: jankakr989
Text: Wow thank you! That actually really does make sense. It’s just kinda funny that EDs start quite often because of low self esteem (like I wanted to just lose couple pounds to “look better” idk how I got here year later) but then it becomes even worse.

Author: aquariumbaby
Text: i think its really interesting actually ! the psychology behind it is kinda wacky. but supposedly we just dont even acknowledge compliments as compliments or hold onto those positive comments unless we feel like we deserve them. if we applied this logic to eating disorders, it makes a lot of sense when people talk about how many compliments they receive at gws, during relapses, etc.  because, in a lot of cases, they may receive compliments often, but their brain just doesn't acknowledge them during times it doesnt want to accept it. (sorry if my wording is bad, im not a master at explaining things)
